title: Living Cultures Collection 08of13 The Last Bedu of Petra and Wad
description: Living Cultures: Collection Culture Documentary hosted by Paul Bandey, published by ZED in 2012 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/8/85/Living-Cultures-Collection-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Living Cultures: Collection 8) The Last Bedu of Petra and Wadi Rum (Jordan) Abu Lafi is an old Bedouin from Petra. He comes from the Bdoul community, and is from one of the last families to live in a cave inside the archeological site of Petra. Classified as a World Heritage Site since 1985, Petra has become Jordan's biggest tourist attraction, and it provides for Abu Lafi and his family. But because of the development of tourism, the ancient Bedouin traditions are disappearing. Abu Lafi wants to prevent this from happening.
